1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 54-12-33 and 54-12-33.1 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to duties of the human trafficking commission and immunity for reporting
3 human trafficking; and to provide a continuing appropriation.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 54-12-33 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 54-12-33. Human trafficking commission.
8 1. The attorney general mayshall establish a human trafficking commission, comprised of
9 designees from state, local, and tribal agencies which have contact with victims or
10 perpetrators, nongovernmental organizations that represent or work with victims, and
11 other organizations and individuals, including victims, whose expertise would benefit
12 the commission. The attorney general may establish the commission by appointing an
13 existing statewide coalition.
14 2. The commission shall:
15 a. Collect and evaluate data on human trafficking in this state and submit an annual
16 report to the attorney general, governor, and legislative assembly;
17 b. Promote awareness and provide information to education personnel and the
18 general public about human trafficking, victim remedies and services, and
19 trafficking prevention;
20 c. Promote training on human trafficking prevention and victim services for state
21 and local employees and members of regulated occupations and professions
22 who may have recurring contact with victims or perpetrators;
23 d. Promote training on human trafficking investigation and prosecution and on
24 missing and murdered indigenous people with the North Dakota state's attorney's
