7 f. Conduct other appropriate activities.
8 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 54-12-33.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
9 amended and reenacted as follows:
10 54-12-33.1. Human trafficking prevention training - Exemptions - Immunity -
11 Continuing appropriation.
12 1. As used in this section:
13 a. "Human trafficking" means human trafficking as defined in chapter 12.1-41.
14 b. "Human trafficking commission" means the commission established under
15 section 54-12-33.
16 c. "Lodging establishment" means any hotel, motel, resort, building, or structure that
17 is used to provide sleeping accommodations to transient guests.
18 d. "Proprietor" means the person in charge of a lodging establishment and includes
19 an owner, lessee, and manager.
20 e. "Regulated occupation or profession" includes a profession regulated by the
21 education standards and practices board, an occupation or profession regulated
22 under title 43, and an attorney licensed to practice law in this state.
23 2. Within ninety days of the effective date of this section, theThe human trafficking
24 commission shall establish an educational training program with a focus on the
25 accurate and prompt identification and reporting of, or response to, suspected human
26 trafficking. To the extent possible, the human trafficking commission shall allow the use
27 of existing training modules and materials. The training must include:
28 a. Human trafficking awareness;
29 b. How to recognize potential victims of human trafficking;
30 c. How to identify activities commonly associated with human trafficking; and
